clinical_study.brief_title: A Multicenter, Open-Label Retreatment Study of the Safety and Effectiveness of PN40082 for Lip Augmentation
clinical_study.official_title: A Multicenter, Open-Label Retreatment Study of the Safety and Effectiveness of PN40082 for Lip Augmentation

brief_summary.textblock: To evaluate the safety and efficacy of retreatment with PN40082 for lip augmentation.

detailed_description.textblock: This is a multicenter, open-label clinical study of retreatment of subjects seeking lip augmentation who received treatment with either PN40082 or Restylane Silk in prior Protocol PRO 2018-02 (NCT04032977). Subjects meeting the inclusion/exclusion criteria will receive a single additional treatment with PN40082

study_design_info.intervention_model_description: multicenter, open-label clinical study of retreatment of subjects seeking lip augmentation

primary_outcome.measure: Change From Baseline in Lip Fullness Grading Scale
primary_outcome.description: Lip Fullness Grading Scale is a validated 5-point photonumeric rating scale with 0 being very thin lips (worse outcome) up to 4 full lips (best outcome)

primary_outcome.measure: Change From Baseline in Perioral Lines Severity Scale
primary_outcome.description: Change from baseline in the perioral lines rating scale (POL), a 4 point rating scale with 0 as a mouth with no perioral lines (better outcome) to 3 a mouth with many deep lines or crevices (worse outcome).

secondary_outcome.measure: Number of Participants With Patient Global Aesthetic Improvement
secondary_outcome.description: Change from baseline for the patient Global Aesthetic Improvement scale, a 5 point scale with 1= the appearance is worse than the original condition (worse outcome) up to 5 very much improved optimal cosmetic result (better outcome)

secondary_outcome.measure: Number of Participants With Investigator Global Aesthetic Improvement
secondary_outcome.description: Change from baseline in the Investigator Global Aesthetic Improvement score, a 5 point scale with 1= the appearance is worse than the original condition (worse outcome) up to 5 = very much improved optimal cosmetic result (better outcome)

secondary_outcome.measure: Number of Subjects With Decreased Swelling
secondary_outcome.description: Swelling Assessment at Visit 3/Month 2, a 4 point scale with 0 = no swelling (better outcome) up to 4= Severe Swelling (worse outcome)

arm_group.description: All subjects in this study will receive one open-label treatment with PN40082.

intervention.description: PN40082 (manufactured by Prollenium Medical Technologies) is a clear, colorless gel in 1.0 mL pre-filled syringes with 25 mg/mL of stabilized hyaluronic acid and lidocaine 0.3% w/w.

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
1. In Protocol PRO 2018-02, the subject was in the per-protocol population, i.e., met all inclusion/exclusion criteria; received study device, completed Visit 5 within the specified window; had LFGS score by the Blinded Evaluating Investigator at Visit 3/Month 2, and had no significant protocol violations that would affect the treatment evaluation.
2. If female and of childbearing potential, a negative urine pregnancy test at Visit 1/Day 1 and the subject agrees to use adequate contraception during the study period
3. Willing to give written informed consent
Exclusion Criteria:
1. Women who are pregnant, lactating, or planning a pregnancy

reported_events.time_frame: Adverse events were collected from the time the subject signed informed consent until discharged from the study, approximately 3 months. Follow-up procedures related to pregnancy, AEs, SAEs or AESIs could continue beyond the end of the study, an average of 6 months.
